        "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies",
        "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior experimental and computational studies on hemolysis in rotary blood pumps, including the Giersiepen power-law model calibration dataset, the Heuser-Opitz shear exposure studies, and the Taskin et al. CFD validation corpus. This synthesis informed the selection of hemolysis model constants and the definition of acceptance thresholds used throughout the credibility assessment. The body of evidence spans more than a decade of published literature and is considered sufficiently mature to serve as background context for model parameter selection."
